 increasingly difficult economic circumstances, and the terrible effects of the great earthquake and fire of 1923. This crucial decade of Japanese history set the stage for the shattering events of the 1930s and 1940s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 7aHISTORY / Military / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311070421140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476535040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804765350423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804765350.jpg  a978-3-11-070421-1  SUP eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles